---

## **The Basic Loop**

```javascript
// Track every seed variant the user generates + their reaction
const seedFeedback = {
  seed1: {
    trials: 15,
    accepted: 12,           // Accepted/committed
    edited: 2,              // Accepted but heavily modified
    rejected: 1,            // Discarded
    acceptanceRate: 0.8,    // P(user likes seed 1)
    avgEditsPerAccept: 0.17 // How much work needed
  },
  seed2: {
    trials: 12,
    accepted: 6,
    edited: 4,
    rejected: 2,
    acceptanceRate: 0.5,
    avgEditsPerAccept: 0.67
  },
  seed3: {
    trials: 8,
    accepted: 7,
    edited: 0,
    rejected: 1,
    acceptanceRate: 0.875,  // Highest confidence
    avgEditsPerAccept: 0
  }
};
```

**Now use probability:**

```javascript
// Expected value of using each seed (lower = better)
function expectedCostOfSeed(seed) {
  const data = seedFeedback[seed];

  return (data.acceptanceRate * 0) +           // Free if accepted
         (data.editRate * data.avgEditsPerAccept) +  // Cost of edits
         (data.rejectionRate * 999);           // Huge cost if rejected
}

// E(seed1) = 0.8*0 + 0.13*0.17 + 0.07*999 = 70.48
// E(seed2) = 0.5*0 + 0.33*0.67 + 0.17*999 = 170.39
// E(seed3) = 0.875*0 + 0*0 + 0.125*999 = 124.88

// Result: seed3 > seed1 > seed2 (recommend seed3)
```

